descriptor_multigrid_score_grid_prefix13                     ../fp_multigrid_generation/resid_078
descriptor_multigrid_score_grid_prefix14                     ../fp_multigrid_generation/resid_remaining
multigrid_score_individual_rec_ensemble                      no
multigrid_score_weights_text                                 no
descriptor_multigrid_score_fp_ref_mol                        yes
descriptor_multigrid_score_footprint_ref                     ../fp_multigrid_generation/lig.mol2
descriptor_multigrid_score_foot_compare_type                 Euclidean
-------------------------------------------------------------
You chose to use the Euclidean distance as the metric 
to compare the footprints.  When the value is 0 then 
there is perfect agreement between the two footprints.
As the agreement gets worse between the two
footprints the value increases.
-------------------------------------------------------------
descriptor_multigrid_score_normalize_foot                    yes
-------------------------------------------------------------
You chose to normalize footprints which penalizes
the score of the pose if the footprint is bad.
-------------------------------------------------------------
descriptor_multigrid_score_vdw_norm_scale                    1
descriptor_multigrid_score_es_norm_scale                     1

--- Descriptor Score Parameters: Pharmacophore ---
descriptor_fms_score_use_ref_mol2                            yes
descriptor_fms_score_ref_mol2_filename                       ../fp_multigrid_generation/lig.mol2
descriptor_fms_score_write_reference_pharmacophore_mol2      no
descriptor_fms_score_write_reference_pharmacophore_txt       no
descriptor_fms_score_write_candidate_pharmacophore           no
descriptor_fms_score_write_matched_pharmacophore             no
descriptor_fms_score_compare_type                            overlap
-------------------------------------------------------------
You are using a ligand based reference for computing the FMS.
When the value is 0 then there is a perfect overlap.
When the value is negative then you have multi-matched ph4.
When the value is positive then you have matches with residual.
-------------------------------------------------------------
descriptor_fms_score_full_match                              yes
descriptor_fms_score_match_rate_weight                       5.0
descriptor_fms_score_match_dist_cutoff                       1.0
descriptor_fms_score_match_proj_cutoff                       0.7071
descriptor_fms_score_max_score                               20

--- Descriptor Score Parameters: Fingerprint / Tanimoto ---
descriptor_fingerprint_ref_filename                          ../fp_multigrid_generation/lig.mol2

--- Descriptor Score Parameters: Hungarian Matching Similarity ---
descriptor_hms_score_ref_filename                            ../fp_multigrid_generation/lig.mol2
descriptor_hms_score_matching_coeff                          -5
descriptor_hms_score_rmsd_coeff                              1

--- Descriptor Score Parameters: Volume Overlap Score ---
descriptor_volume_score_reference_mol2_filename              ../fp_multigrid_generation/lig.mol2
descriptor_volume_score_overlap_compute_method               analytical

--- Descriptor Score Weights ---
descriptor_weight_multigrid_score                            1
descriptor_weight_pharmacophore_score                        1
descriptor_weight_fingerprint_tanimoto                       1
descriptor_weight_hms_score                                  1
descriptor_weight_volume_overlap_score                       1

Using these settings, the Descriptor Score function takes the form:
Descriptor_Score = (1 * Multigrid_Score) + (1 * Pharmacophore_Similarity_Score) + (1 * Tanimoto) + (1 * Hungarian_Matching_Similarity_Score) + (1 * Volume_Score)

